WEBVTT

00:02.596 --> 00:04.356
[CHELSEA COUGHING]

00:09.191 --> 00:10.519
[CHELSEA BLOWS NOSE]

00:13.620 --> 00:15.982
- Chelsea?
CHELSEA: Yeah?

00:16.717 --> 00:17.773
You okay?

00:20.114 --> 00:22.805
I think I'm coming down with a cold.

00:22.979 --> 00:24.443
[NOSE HONKS]

00:27.108 --> 00:32.034
That doesn't sound like a cold.
It sounds like quitting time in Bedrock.

00:32.203 --> 00:33.758
Do I feel hot to you?

00:34.268 --> 00:36.425
- Let me see.
- Stop it.

00:37.365 --> 00:38.830
You're supposed to feel my head.

00:39.231 --> 00:41.491
Yeah, but those babies
are my frame of reference.

00:42.495 --> 00:43.925
[COUGHS]

00:44.093 --> 00:47.453
- Maybe I should go home.
- Lf you think that's the right thing to do.

00:47.623 --> 00:51.416
Charlie, it's the middle of the night
and I'm sick. I'm not going home.

00:52.152 --> 00:54.809
- Then why did you say you were?
- I was testing you.

00:55.716 --> 00:59.440
Yeah, well, I knew that,
and I was testing you.

00:59.612 --> 01:01.735
I think we both did very well.

01:03.242 --> 01:04.571
[COUGHS]

01:05.208 --> 01:07.763
Tell you what,
you get a good night's sleep.

01:07.939 --> 01:10.993
- I'm sure you'll feel better in the morning.
- Where are you going?

01:11.469 --> 01:14.398
I'm gonna crash on the couch,
let you have the whole bed to yourself.

01:14.799 --> 01:16.660
Really?
You're gonna leave me here alone?

01:17.330 --> 01:20.884
No, no. I just thought
you might want your own space.

01:21.526 --> 01:24.455
You know, when dogs are sick,
they hide till they feel better.

01:26.922 --> 01:29.545
Probably why they're man's best friend.

01:30.418 --> 01:31.814
Could you please stay?

01:34.315 --> 01:35.540
Pretty please?

01:37.245 --> 01:38.642
How can I say no?

01:40.776 --> 01:42.966
Seriously, how?

01:44.006 --> 01:46.028
Spoon?

01:46.937 --> 01:48.401
[CHARLIE SIGHS]

01:48.569 --> 01:50.692
Try and stop me.

01:53.931 --> 01:55.589
[CHARLIE SIGHS]

01:57.661 --> 01:58.784
[COUGHS]

01:58.960 --> 02:00.424
[HACKS]

02:03.256 --> 02:05.742
So, what,
are you just gonna swallow that?

02:06.020 --> 02:08.007
Go to sleep.

02:11.848 --> 02:13.403
[CHARLIE SIGHS]

02:16.810 --> 02:18.173
What are you doing?

02:18.343 --> 02:21.465
Come on, you know what happens
when we spoon.

02:21.639 --> 02:23.433
I'm sick.

02:23.605 --> 02:26.000
Obviously so am I.

02:27.467 --> 02:28.830
All right, fine.

02:30.698 --> 02:32.356
Go ahead.

02:35.927 --> 02:38.516
This is another test, isn't it?

02:40.000 --> 02:46.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:07.765 --> 03:10.251
<i>ANNOUNCER [ON TV]: Coming up next
on Turner Classic Movies:</i>

03:10.429 --> 03:13.222
<i>The Bridges of Madison County.</i>

03:16.458 --> 03:18.581
I am not gonna cry.

03:21.020 --> 03:22.246
Hey.

03:22.752 --> 03:23.774
What are you doing up?

03:24.351 --> 03:26.542
Watching a Clint Eastwood movie.

03:29.812 --> 03:30.835
What are you doing up?

03:31.245 --> 03:32.573
Chelsea's sick.

03:32.743 --> 03:35.172
She was coughing and sneezing
all over the place.

03:35.341 --> 03:36.363
Oh, no.

03:36.540 --> 03:38.935
Yeah. I had to wait
until she finally fell asleep...

03:39.104 --> 03:41.761
...so I could get out of there
without pissing her off.

03:42.235 --> 03:43.393
How considerate.

03:44.932 --> 03:48.361
What do you want from me?
I'm not a big phlegm fan.

03:50.694 --> 03:53.987
- This isn't a Clint Eastwood movie.
- Yes, it is.

03:54.656 --> 03:57.847
Even Clint Eastwood doesn't think
this is a Clint Eastwood movie.

03:58.020 --> 03:59.315
Well, tough. I like it.

03:59.485 --> 04:02.313
Sure you do.
You're a giant fruit basket.

04:02.483 --> 04:04.810
I'll never apologize for my feminine side.

04:07.313 --> 04:08.572
[CHARLIE SIGHS]

04:08.744 --> 04:10.265
Boy, I hope she gets better soon.

04:10.443 --> 04:12.872
This sick stuff
is not what I signed on for.

04:14.839 --> 04:18.733
You're kidding, right?
This is exactly what you signed on for.

04:20.134 --> 04:23.256
You told Chelsea you loved her.
You gave her an engagement ring.

04:23.431 --> 04:26.553
This is what it's all about,
being there for her no matter what.

04:26.728 --> 04:29.714
For richer or poorer, better or worse,
in sickness and in health.

04:30.325 --> 04:34.946
Call me crazy,
but I prefer richer, better and health.

04:36.153 --> 04:38.844
Well, regardless,
this could be a real opportunity for you.

04:39.783 --> 04:42.269
Opportunity for what,
a massive infection?

04:42.781 --> 04:45.336
An opportunity to show her
that she can depend on you...

04:45.511 --> 04:47.771
...that you're not just there
for the good times.

04:47.943 --> 04:50.134
Okay, I hear that.

04:50.307 --> 04:51.931
- Tell me one thing.
- Yeah?

04:52.106 --> 04:53.661
What's in it for me?

04:55.869 --> 04:57.958
Watch Clint and Meryl.

04:58.333 --> 04:59.991
Learn how to love.

05:04.828 --> 05:07.814
I'll take my chances in the snot locker.

05:08.991 --> 05:11.648
[TV PLAYING INDISTINCTLY]

05:13.020 --> 05:15.109
I will not cry.

05:19.715 --> 05:21.736
CHELSEA:
Charlie?

05:23.178 --> 05:25.165
You awake?

05:27.175 --> 05:28.231
[SIGHS]

05:40.963 --> 05:42.984
Boy, I hope not.

05:44.493 --> 05:46.480
I feel awful.

05:46.957 --> 05:48.546
Really?

05:48.922 --> 05:50.749
You look swell.

05:51.320 --> 05:52.410
I should go home.

05:52.586 --> 05:55.912
No, no, no.
I am not falling for that again.

05:56.082 --> 05:58.637
You stay right here,
let me take care of you.

05:58.813 --> 06:01.039
You mean it?

06:01.211 --> 06:03.573
Oh, man.
Do I have to mean it too?

06:05.274 --> 06:08.101
Just kidding.
Can I make you some tea or something?

06:08.271 --> 06:10.860
- Yes, please.
- Coming up.

06:11.036 --> 06:13.931
- With honey.
- Sure.

06:14.100 --> 06:15.860
And maybe an English muffin.

06:17.297 --> 06:18.556
No problem.

06:18.729 --> 06:19.887
Toasted crispy.

06:22.492 --> 06:23.514
Right.

06:23.691 --> 06:26.552
And let the butter melt
into all the nooks and crannies...

06:26.722 --> 06:28.277
...before you put the jam on.

06:30.385 --> 06:31.849
Anything else?

06:32.017 --> 06:34.072
Can I have a hug?

06:40.743 --> 06:42.002
Try and stop me.

06:54.997 --> 06:56.893
- Nice necklace.
- Thanks.

06:57.062 --> 06:59.753
- Buy it for yourself?
- No, a girl gave it to me.

07:00.725 --> 07:02.655
Really? She must like you.

07:02.823 --> 07:05.378
Yeah, she's nuts for me.

07:05.554 --> 07:09.039
- Well, is she cute?
- I guess.

07:09.583 --> 07:12.172
- You don't seem very happy about it.
- I'm not.

07:13.113 --> 07:15.872
- Why, what's the problem?
- She's nine.

07:19.375 --> 07:21.804
Nine? Where would you meet
a nine-year-old girl?

07:22.272 --> 07:24.532
We're in the same math class.

07:26.402 --> 07:28.389
Is, uh...
Is she one of those advanced students?

07:28.900 --> 07:30.330
Sadly no.

07:31.864 --> 07:33.691
But she does help me
with my homework.

07:36.326 --> 07:38.120
Hey, Berta.

07:38.291 --> 07:41.516
Chelsea's not feeling well.
Could you make her tea and English muffin?

07:41.955 --> 07:43.113
Sure, I could.

07:46.751 --> 07:48.544
But you won't.

07:48.715 --> 07:50.543
Is that what you're saying?

07:50.713 --> 07:51.871
[SIGHS]

07:53.045 --> 07:56.439
- Where are the muffins?
- In the fridge, as always.

07:56.942 --> 07:58.463
Don't condescend to me.

07:59.139 --> 08:01.535
He does it to me all the time.
It's very irritating.

08:02.336 --> 08:03.426
No one's talking to you.

08:03.602 --> 08:04.828
See? Like that.

08:05.001 --> 08:06.466
That wasn't condescending.

08:06.633 --> 08:08.097
But that was, right?

08:09.297 --> 08:10.886
Right.

08:11.861 --> 08:14.325
Boy, as soon as I get my license,
I am so out of here.

08:14.492 --> 08:17.853
Sure. You can drive your girlfriend
to Gymboree.

08:18.655 --> 08:20.177
At least I have a girlfriend.

08:23.818 --> 08:25.645
[MOCKING TONE]
"At least I have a girlfriend."

08:27.947 --> 08:30.173
So, what's the deal?
Does, uh, Chelsea have a cold?

08:30.345 --> 08:33.831
Not sure. Cold, flu.
Something disgusting.

08:35.041 --> 08:36.732
Maybe she has an STD.

08:37.738 --> 08:40.634
- What?
- I mean sexually transmitted disease.

08:41.068 --> 08:42.727
I know what STD's are.

08:43.232 --> 08:44.663
Your uncle helped invent them.

08:48.263 --> 08:50.783
You know they can be prevented
by using a condom.

08:50.960 --> 08:53.924
I know we could've prevented you
by using a condom.

08:55.623 --> 08:57.587
Now we gotta use a hammer.

08:59.219 --> 09:00.241
I don't understand.

09:00.419 --> 09:02.746
Go get me a hammer and I'll show you.

09:04.582 --> 09:05.944
Okay.

09:09.077 --> 09:10.769
You must be so proud.

09:12.141 --> 09:14.730
JAKE:
Ballpeen or claw hammer?

09:16.104 --> 09:19.589
Do me a favor.
When he comes back, just do it.

09:22.465 --> 09:26.019
Okay. Here we go. Room service.

09:27.661 --> 09:29.921
Chelsea? Honey?

09:30.091 --> 09:33.577
CHELSEA: Don't come in.
- Wasn't even tempted.

09:35.453 --> 09:37.179
I got your tea and muffins.

09:37.352 --> 09:41.474
CHELSEA:
Oh, I have diarrhea. I can't eat now.

09:42.081 --> 09:43.705
I may never eat again.

09:45.212 --> 09:47.539
CHELSEA: Would you mind going
to the drugstore for me?

09:48.276 --> 09:51.035
For you, I'd go to the ends of the earth.

09:51.207 --> 09:53.965
Coming back's a whole other question.

09:54.470 --> 09:57.729
CHELSEA: What?
- I said what do you need?

09:57.901 --> 10:01.421
CHELSEA: Well, I need Pepto and we're
almost out of tissues.

10:01.597 --> 10:05.117
And I need some decongestant,
some cough syrup...

10:05.294 --> 10:08.553
...something for canker sores
and wet wipes.

10:08.724 --> 10:09.950
For your hands?

10:10.123 --> 10:12.178
- No.
- Got it.

10:14.319 --> 10:17.510
And I'm probably gonna need
some tampons.

10:17.683 --> 10:20.771
Oh, great. There's gonna be blood too.

10:22.179 --> 10:25.574
CHELSEA: You're really being wonderful
about all this, Charlie.

10:25.742 --> 10:29.172
Oh, It's nothing. It's what a guy does
when he loves somebody.

10:30.805 --> 10:32.167
Ah. Should have known.

10:32.337 --> 10:36.096
The second you give them a ring
they fall out of warranty.

10:44.959 --> 10:46.719
- Hey, Russell.
- Mm-hm.

10:46.890 --> 10:50.047
- What's good for canker sores?
- You got canker sores?

10:50.221 --> 10:51.243
No. My girlfriend.

10:51.853 --> 10:54.578
- What do you recommend?
- Tennis shoes.

10:55.349 --> 10:58.074
- Excuse me?
- Put them on and run away.

10:58.247 --> 11:00.733
There's a lot of broads out there.
Find a clean one.

11:02.310 --> 11:03.502
[CHARLIE SIGHS]

11:03.676 --> 11:06.231
I can't run away.
I'm kind of engaged to her.

11:06.406 --> 11:08.870
Oh, Charlie. No.

11:09.037 --> 11:10.626
Yep, I bit the bullet.

11:10.802 --> 11:11.824
[SIGHS]

11:12.002 --> 11:13.160
You bit the big one.

11:14.100 --> 11:17.529
Hey, just because you blew three marriages
doesn't mean I can't make this work.

11:18.129 --> 11:19.321
[LAUGHS]

11:19.495 --> 11:21.153
You're a funny guy, Charlie.

11:21.326 --> 11:23.915
And that's not just
the OxyContin talking.

11:25.290 --> 11:28.378
Here you go. Cank Be Gone.

11:28.554 --> 11:31.415
- What else?
- Ah, let's see. Cough syrup.

11:31.584 --> 11:34.809
- Regular or codeine?
- Don't you need a prescription for codeine?

11:34.981 --> 11:36.570
What are you, a cop?

11:38.878 --> 11:42.171
Here. I'll give you the kid stuff.

11:42.341 --> 11:43.397
What else?

11:43.573 --> 11:47.559
Uh, tissues, throat lozenges, decongestant,
Pepto, wet wipes.

11:48.103 --> 11:51.588
Jeez, where did you find this one,
a hospital parking lot?

11:52.099 --> 11:53.495
Come on, Russell. Help me out.

11:53.664 --> 11:55.651
Okay. Okay. Here you go.

11:55.829 --> 11:56.851
[RUSSELL SIGHS]

11:57.028 --> 11:59.889
A dam for every river...

12:00.059 --> 12:02.750
...a plug for every jug.

12:03.989 --> 12:06.578
Oh, right. I almost forgot.
She also needs tampons.

12:06.752 --> 12:08.047
Oh, lucky you.

12:08.219 --> 12:09.342
[CHUCKLES]

12:09.517 --> 12:10.539
What size?

12:11.416 --> 12:13.277
How should I know?

12:13.580 --> 12:17.838
Is there some kind of a condom-tampon
conversion chart?

12:18.542 --> 12:20.563
No. But that's an amusing idea.

12:20.740 --> 12:21.762
[CHUCKLES]

12:21.940 --> 12:26.300
Actually, it's not about size per se,
it's more about flow.

12:27.135 --> 12:31.188
See, that's a piece of information I could've
gone the rest of my life without knowing.

12:32.663 --> 12:34.991
Here you go. Here's a variety pack.

12:35.161 --> 12:39.021
This will handle anything
from a little drizzle to a monsoon.

12:41.189 --> 12:44.051
Listen, is it too late
to change my mind about the codeine?

12:47.817 --> 12:49.872
The first one's free.

12:50.048 --> 12:51.273
<i>[MOUTHS]
Thank you.</i>

12:56.309 --> 12:57.898
[COUGHS]

13:00.905 --> 13:02.029
Okay.

13:02.204 --> 13:03.260
Got all of your stuff.

13:03.435 --> 13:04.593
Took you long enough.

13:04.768 --> 13:08.561
Whoa, whoa, I just went shopping
from wet wipes and tampons.

13:08.731 --> 13:10.457
I'm allowed to take my time.

13:10.962 --> 13:12.449
Sorry. You mad at me?

13:13.060 --> 13:15.751
No. No. Why would I be mad at you?

13:15.925 --> 13:18.514
Because I'm sick
and you have to take care of me.

13:18.688 --> 13:19.710
[SCOFFS]

13:19.888 --> 13:22.818
Are you kidding me?
I love taking care of you.

13:22.985 --> 13:24.950
I just love...

13:27.048 --> 13:28.672
...it.

13:28.846 --> 13:31.072
Yeah, I can see that.

13:31.511 --> 13:32.907
Listen.

13:33.076 --> 13:36.937
Can you go over to my place and get me
some clean clothes and feed Sir Lancelot?

13:37.772 --> 13:39.396
- Who?
- My cat.

13:41.069 --> 13:43.124
He's not gonna feed himself, Charlie.

13:43.300 --> 13:45.820
Are you sure? Maybe you've got mice.

13:46.264 --> 13:49.092
Oh, you're probably gonna have
to change the litter box too.

13:50.161 --> 13:52.250
Change it into what?

13:52.825 --> 13:55.720
You got to scoop out the poop
and put in fresh litter.

13:56.522 --> 13:59.644
Oh, this just keeps getting better
and better.

14:00.185 --> 14:01.377
Charlie.

14:01.550 --> 14:03.810
- Yeah?
- I love you.

14:04.281 --> 14:05.905
Great.

14:06.446 --> 14:07.775
Aren't you gonna say it back?

14:09.177 --> 14:11.198
I'm gonna go pan for cat turds.

14:12.607 --> 14:15.197
If that doesn't say I love you,
nothing does.

14:18.002 --> 14:20.364
I promise, I'm wearing it.

14:20.533 --> 14:22.225
Wait a sec.

14:26.029 --> 14:27.653
Okay, I sent you a picture.

14:27.828 --> 14:29.655
Now what's the answer to number four?

14:29.826 --> 14:31.586
Oh, yeah, that's what I had.

14:35.620 --> 14:37.175
- What you doing Alan?
- My taxes.

14:37.352 --> 14:39.872
I promised myself I wouldn't wait
till the last minute.

14:40.050 --> 14:42.842
Yeah, you promised me
you'd only stay here for a few days...

14:43.014 --> 14:44.410
...so your word means nothing.

14:46.044 --> 14:48.701
- You're driving me to Chelsea's.
- Why don't you drive yourself?

14:48.875 --> 14:51.270
Because I just chugged
a half a bottle of codeine...

14:51.440 --> 14:55.028
...and this bourbon might make me
a bit of a threat on the road.

14:55.703 --> 14:57.667
Ah, good call.

15:00.432 --> 15:01.658
Here kitty, kitty.

15:01.830 --> 15:02.818
[CLICKS TONGUE]

15:02.996 --> 15:05.051
Here kitty, kitty, kitty.

15:05.227 --> 15:07.350
Okay, I got her clean clothes.

15:07.526 --> 15:11.148
Great.
Now I just gotta feed the damn cat.

15:11.321 --> 15:13.512
Come on, Sir Lancelot.

15:13.687 --> 15:15.276
Come out and eat your kibble.

15:15.452 --> 15:16.677
[SIR LANCELOT CATERWAULS]

15:16.850 --> 15:18.008
Ow!

15:18.616 --> 15:20.875
Son of a bitch.

15:21.047 --> 15:25.203
I'm pretty sure if you just put the food out,
he'll find it and eat it when he's hungry.

15:25.376 --> 15:27.203
Really? Think if he was that smart...

15:27.374 --> 15:29.963
...he'd just crap in the toilet
instead of a litter box.

15:30.805 --> 15:32.496
Oh, uh, did you change the litter yet?

15:33.236 --> 15:35.699
No, I was actually gonna
offer you $20 to do it.

15:36.400 --> 15:38.421
I'll take it. Ha, ha.

15:38.598 --> 15:39.722
Deal.

15:39.896 --> 15:42.224
Ha, ha. I would have done it for 10.

15:42.395 --> 15:44.325
Ha, ha.
I would have given you a thousand.

15:48.921 --> 15:50.011
Whoa.

15:50.187 --> 15:51.913
Big cat.

15:53.817 --> 15:55.475
You know what I just realized, Alan?

15:55.915 --> 15:58.379
Cough syrup and hard liquor don't mix?

15:59.313 --> 16:01.470
No, they're delightful.

16:02.577 --> 16:05.768
I'm thinking sooner or later Chelsea's
gonna wanna move in with me.

16:05.940 --> 16:09.233
Yeah, you marry her
that's the chance you take.

16:10.702 --> 16:14.063
And she's probably gonna
wanna bring Sir Craps-A-Lot.

16:15.598 --> 16:16.790
You never know.

16:16.963 --> 16:19.291
He might want to get his own place.

16:20.194 --> 16:22.454
I'm guessing he will before you will.

16:23.391 --> 16:24.617
Oh, Lord.

16:24.790 --> 16:26.686
This cat's been eating more than kibble.

16:27.421 --> 16:29.714
This turd's got feathers.

16:32.849 --> 16:34.938
You know there's a real chance
that someday...

16:35.114 --> 16:37.101
...without any kind of warning
whatsoever...

16:37.279 --> 16:39.505
...Chelsea will up and decide
to get sick again.

16:40.043 --> 16:43.472
We're on the air with codeine and bourbon.
Go ahead caller.

16:44.539 --> 16:46.867
I'm just saying I don't think
I can go through it again.

16:47.037 --> 16:48.626
I'm not cut out to be a caregiver.

16:48.802 --> 16:50.857
Ah, you might not think so
but you're doing it.

16:51.033 --> 16:54.292
You, Charlie Harper, are unselfishly
taking care of the woman you love.

16:55.296 --> 16:56.885
Maybe so, but, uh...

16:57.062 --> 16:59.049
...it's getting harder and harder
to love her.

16:59.226 --> 17:00.588
You don't mean that.

17:00.758 --> 17:06.242
Oh, Alan, if you'd seen and heard
the things I have in the last 24 hours...

17:06.420 --> 17:09.111
...it'd turn you gayer
than a French horn.

17:10.215 --> 17:12.474
Excuse me,
but I have witnessed childbirth.

17:12.646 --> 17:14.167
I saw my son's enormous head...

17:14.346 --> 17:17.208
...poke out of what used to be
one of my very favorite places.

17:18.776 --> 17:20.740
Thanks for the image.

17:20.906 --> 17:24.892
I'll never be able to watch
the kid pull on a sweater again.

17:25.069 --> 17:29.464
If you hang in there, show Chelsea you'll
stick by her even when not at her best...

17:29.666 --> 17:33.493
...she will love you more deeply and
intensely than you could have imagined.

17:33.662 --> 17:34.786
And you know this how?

17:35.227 --> 17:36.283
How else? Chick flicks.

17:38.558 --> 17:41.851
Oh, this is not a kitty cat.

17:42.022 --> 17:44.451
This is a mountain lion.

17:44.919 --> 17:47.382
- Look.
- Hey, hey, hey.

17:58.107 --> 18:01.037
- You need some more orange juice?
- No, thank you.

18:01.204 --> 18:04.066
It was so nice of you to bring some up
without me even asking.

18:04.501 --> 18:06.090
Don't tell Charlie.

18:06.267 --> 18:09.560
It's taken a long time to train him
not to expect anything from me.

18:10.463 --> 18:11.984
Got it.

18:12.894 --> 18:14.086
[BERTA SIGHS]

18:14.260 --> 18:15.884
He really is crazy about you, you know.

18:16.057 --> 18:18.782
- You think?
- Are you kidding?

18:18.955 --> 18:20.579
Charlie doesn't go near sick women.

18:21.020 --> 18:23.483
I mean, physically sick.

18:23.684 --> 18:24.808
Around here...

18:24.983 --> 18:28.912
...one sneeze will get you a cab fare
and a complimentary travel mug.

18:30.179 --> 18:32.699
I have noticed he's trying very hard.

18:32.877 --> 18:37.998
Just remember, when it comes to nurturing,
Charlie's like a dog playing the piano.

18:38.171 --> 18:40.533
You can't fault him
if he hits a few bum notes.

18:41.069 --> 18:44.896
You just got to applaud the effort
and hope he doesn't whiz all over the keys.

18:46.464 --> 18:47.656
I understand.

18:48.895 --> 18:50.792
Thanks, Berta.

18:53.425 --> 18:55.286
Just so we're clear this ain't no hotel.

18:55.456 --> 18:57.647
You need more towels
you get them yourself.

19:01.084 --> 19:02.106
[SIGHS]

19:02.283 --> 19:03.872
Sorry about that.

19:04.049 --> 19:05.808
You really can't expect much from her.

19:06.613 --> 19:07.703
I won't.

19:08.478 --> 19:11.169
Here. I got you clean clothes
and underwear.

19:12.508 --> 19:16.300
The cat's fed
and the litter box is turd free.

19:16.471 --> 19:17.663
Thank you, Charlie.

19:17.837 --> 19:20.198
You have been so wonderful
through all of this.

19:20.367 --> 19:22.830
I have, haven't I?

19:24.198 --> 19:26.059
I just want you to know...

19:26.229 --> 19:28.454
...I am definitely
gonna make it up to you.

19:28.960 --> 19:32.184
Chelsea, to be honest,
that's the only thing that's kept me going.

19:34.421 --> 19:36.352
- Uh-oh.
- Uh-oh, what?

19:39.150 --> 19:40.671
[CHELSEA VOMITS]

19:44.312 --> 19:46.300
Oh, Charlie, I'm so sorry.

19:46.744 --> 19:48.368
No, no. It's okay.

19:48.542 --> 19:49.939
At least it's not wicker.

19:52.439 --> 19:54.233
Excuse me a second.

20:00.432 --> 20:02.090
[CHARLIE VOMITS]

20:06.493 --> 20:08.048
[COUGHING]

20:10.523 --> 20:12.044
[BLOWS NOSE]

20:13.287 --> 20:14.581
[COUGHS]

20:14.752 --> 20:18.737
Okay, I am going to go to the pharmacy
and get your medicine.

20:18.915 --> 20:21.845
If you get it from Russell, count the pills.

20:22.612 --> 20:24.201
Will do.

20:24.643 --> 20:27.107
- Hope you feel better.
- Thanks.

20:27.274 --> 20:29.795
Charlie, you don't mind
Sir Lancelot being here, do you?

20:29.972 --> 20:31.493
No. Not at all.

20:31.670 --> 20:34.133
- I love cats.
- Good.

20:35.334 --> 20:36.424
[COUGHS]

20:36.600 --> 20:37.859
[DOOR CLOSES]

20:38.031 --> 20:40.325
[SCRATCHING]

20:41.461 --> 20:44.448
Don't scratch the door, Sir Lancelot.

20:49.388 --> 20:50.819
Clean my litter box?

20:50.986 --> 20:53.042
Oh, come on. I've been sick.

20:53.617 --> 20:56.308
Fine. I'll just use your facilities.

20:56.749 --> 20:58.872
Not in the tub this time, okay?

21:00.312 --> 21:02.208
Your house, your rules.

21:02.377 --> 21:03.932
[GASPS]

21:04.109 --> 21:06.368
[PANTING]

21:08.904 --> 21:10.232
I'm not going to make it.

21:10.403 --> 21:11.527
[COUGHS]

21:12.468 --> 21:14.591
Yes, you are.

